The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 December is 115,306 (13,289.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 November, there were 5,503 new confirmed cases (634.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 November, there were 5,247 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (256 extra cases).
